comments.body:
@bmanikm I see references to $env:ProgramData in [PowerShellGet](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/master/src/Modules/Shared/PowerShellGet/PSModule.psm1#L46)

Looks like this is used for Nuget provider. In PowerShell Core this provider will be available in-place (no bootstrapping).

It make sense to remove these code paths for PowerShell Core. What do you think?

@bmanikm You mean storing system-wide PowerShellGet settings - for all users, for that PowerShell instance? 

I think /opt/microsoft/powershell must be used for this

@andschwa Does this make sense?
